The Scylla and Amphitrite dynamic was a little lost on me since I never know about those two Greek figures, but barring that, the captain's logs were atmospheric, but ultimately felt kindaflat? His obsession with the dream woman was way too under-explored and left me curious.

The beating heart needing to be dried out to keep the monster down, however, I found to be creative and interesting.

I'll leave it as a novote for me.

I agree with forbiddenquest on the font choice, though. Made some of the text a little annoying to read.







